xrroot -- Yet another wallpaper application...

Q: why another one?
A: Personal requirements..

Q: Why this one?
A: Because it can do stuff, manipulate images etc..

Q: How does it do that?
A: Using imlib2..

Q: how do I install it?
A: like most apps..
       # ./configure
       # make
       # su
       # make install

Q: Where do I report bugs?
A: https://github.com/djpohly/xrroot

Q: uhmm.. help?!?
A: xrroot --help

Q: you don't like docs, right?
A: right...


